## 13. Agent Prompt Guide (portable cheat-sheet)
<!-- A flat, copy-paste summary so ANY coding agent (not just atelier) can build
     on-contract without reading the whole file. Fill from the tokens above with LITERAL
     values, not {token} refs. {{PALETTE_REST}} = the remaining roles, e.g.
     "secondary #… · accent #… · muted #…". Don't hardcode bans here — point at §6. -->
**Palette (use these literally):** primary `{{COLOR_PRIMARY}}` · ink `{{COLOR_FG}}` · paper `{{COLOR_BG}}` · {{PALETTE_REST}}
**Type:** display `{{FONT_DISPLAY}}`, body `{{FONT_BODY}}`. **Spacing:** {{SPACING_SCALE}}. **Radius:** {{RADIUS_SCALE}}. **Depth:** {{DEPTH_STRATEGY}}.

Paste-ready prompts:
- *Landing section:* "Build a hero on `{{COLOR_BG}}` with `{{COLOR_FG}}` text, one `{{COLOR_PRIMARY}}` CTA (loudest pixel at rest), `{{FONT_DISPLAY}}` headline / `{{FONT_BODY}}` body, {{DEPTH_STRATEGY}} depth. Follow the anti-slop rules in §6."
- *Card grid:* "3 cards, {{RADIUS_SCALE}} radius, {{DEPTH_STRATEGY}} elevation, `{{COLOR_PRIMARY}}` only for the primary action; rest/hover/focus states."
- *Form:* "Stacked form, labels in `{{COLOR_FG}}`, inputs inset, focus ring `{{COLOR_PRIMARY}}`, one explicit save; visible `:focus-visible`."
- *Nav:* "Top nav, same background as canvas (`{{COLOR_BG}}`), a subtle border not a different fill; active item in `{{COLOR_PRIMARY}}`."
